SIMPLE: pluperfect
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pluperfect
<hw>Plu"per`fect</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>plus</ets> more + <ets>perfectus</ets> perfect; cf. F.
<ets>plus-que-parfait</ets>, L. <ets>plusquamperfectum</ets>.]</ety>
<def>More than perfect; past perfect; -- said of the tense which denotes
that an action or event was completed at or before the time of another
past action or event.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The pluperfect
tense; also, a verb in the pluperfect tense.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plural</ent>⟦br⟧
